Solution — Exercise 01: GDB Basics
=====================================

Step 1: Load the binary
  gdb ./target

Step 2: Discover what's inside
  (gdb) info functions
  → you will see: success, decoy_a, decoy_b, decoy_c, main

Step 3: Call success() directly
  (gdb) call (void) success()
  → [SUCCESS] You called a hidden function. GDB obeys you now.

Alternative approach:
  (gdb) break main
  (gdb) run
  (gdb) jump success
  → execution jumps to success() instead of continuing main

Why it matters:
  GDB gives you complete control over a running process.
  You can call any function, modify any variable, redirect execution.
  This is the foundation of everything that follows in Horizon.
